
[1]crony

   CRONY, n. [See Crone. But this word seems to carry the sense of
   fellowship; to join, to associate; whence its derivative, an
   associate.] An intimate companion; an associate; a familiar friend.

   To oblige your crony Swift, bring our dame a new years gift.

   Hence, an old crony is an intimate friend of long standing.
